SITE CHARACTERIZATION
Innovative Technology & Technology Transfer
September 15-16, 1994, Washington, D.C.


CONFERENCE OBJECTIVES***
The conference will focus on innovative site characterization technology development and commercialization opportunities via
DOE, DOD and EPA.  At this interactive forum, speakers and panelists from government and industry will also inform attendees
of the latest approaches to site characterization and how innovative technologies can fit into advanced processes and
methodologies.

YOU'LL LEARN ABOUT***

w  DOE site characterization development partnering, demonstrations,
        CRADAs and technology transfers.
w       EPA site characterization technology development programs.
w       How EPA's Vendor Information System for Innovative Monitoring
        & Measuring Technologies (VISIMMT) program is tracking
        characterization technology and how to participate.
w       How to get EPA buy-in for site characterization.
w       Site characterization opportunities in DOD's SCAPS program.
w       The latest integrated characterization approaches utilized by the
        private sector.
                        ... so you can gain that competitive edge.

